We're prepping OR 4.

30:15.728 --> 30:17.898
We're still trying to
reach his next of kin.

30:46.489 --> 30:48.560
All clear. Shocking.

30:56.175 --> 30:57.878
<i>All clear.</i>

31:46.442 --> 31:48.614
Solloway?

31:52.387 --> 31:54.625
Hey.

31:54.626 --> 31:56.529
Sorry it took me a while to get here.

31:56.530 --> 32:00.737
They never let us know
who's coming through.

32:00.738 --> 32:04.010
I hope that Warden Hagan
wasn't too much of a hard-ass.

32:04.011 --> 32:08.218
He can really lay down the law,

32:08.219 --> 32:10.724
but, he's actually a good guy,

32:10.725 --> 32:14.364
once you get to know him.

32:14.365 --> 32:17.371
- No. He was fine. Thanks.
- Good.

32:19.843 --> 32:22.849
You don't remember me, do you?

32:25.688 --> 32:29.093
You... you look...
you look familiar.

32:29.094 --> 32:31.031
- I...
- No, I don't.

32:33.236 --> 32:35.039
John Gunther.

32:45.460 --> 32:47.731
I'm from Bloomsburg.

32:47.732 --> 32:49.569
Bloomsburg, Pennsylvania?

32:52.608 --> 32:53.943
No shit.

32:53.944 --> 32:55.647
We've actually met.

32:55.648 --> 32:57.584
It was high school. Yeah.

32:57.585 --> 32:59.487
Swim meets.

32:59.488 --> 33:01.124
Remember All-County '85?

33:01.125 --> 33:02.627
You took the whole thing.

33:02.628 --> 33:04.263
It was impressive.

33:04.264 --> 33:07.436
I was just in the back
somewhere drowning.

33:09.976 --> 33:11.712
Sure. Yeah. I...

33:11.713 --> 33:14.585
Yeah. You don't remember me.

33:14.586 --> 33:18.225
It's okay.

33:18.226 --> 33:20.395
I've been following your career.

33:20.396 --> 33:23.001
Pretty impressive stuff.

33:23.002 --> 33:27.744
Well, it hasn't exactly
worked out that well for me.

33:27.745 --> 33:31.351
Shit happens.

33:32.688 --> 33:34.257
Hey, look. I'm,

33:34.258 --> 33:36.763
gonna keep an eye out
for you, all right?

33:39.636 --> 33:41.371
Thank you.

33:44.044 --> 33:46.982
You know, over the years, I've
wanted to reach out to you,

33:46.983 --> 33:50.489
but I just never really...

33:50.490 --> 33:51.993
but here you are.

33:54.966 --> 33:58.238
Fucking Noah Solloway.

33:58.239 --> 34:00.176
Okay.

34:02.582 --> 34:05.018
Mr. Solloway?

34:08.025 --> 34:10.029
Mr. Solloway?

34:12.300 --> 34:15.672
- How do you feel?
- Terrible.

34:15.674 --> 34:17.510
Well, these should help with that.

34:17.511 --> 34:20.114
That's one Zofran plus
two Percocet for pain.

34:20.116 --> 34:22.721
Here. Let me lift your head up.

34:22.722 --> 34:24.726
There you go.

34:37.717 --> 34:41.257
Can you tell me
what the date is today?

34:41.257 --> 34:45.498
September 24th.

34:45.500 --> 34:48.371
That's right. Do you know where you are?

34:48.371 --> 34:52.112
- In the hospital.
- Do you know why?

34:52.112 --> 34:55.351
- I had surgery.
- Very good.

34:55.353 --> 34:57.891
Well, you're lucky to be alive, Mr.
Solloway.

34:57.892 --> 35:00.062
Wait. What happened? What... wh...

35:00.063 --> 35:02.366
- How did I get here?
- I don't know all the details,

35:02.367 --> 35:04.838
but your wife may be able to tell you.

35:04.839 --> 35:06.675
My wife?

35:06.676 --> 35:08.913
She just stepped out to use the ladies'.

35:08.914 --> 35:10.850
She'll be so happy to see you awake.

35:10.851 --> 35:12.988
Wait. Who... who are you...
who are you talking about?

35:14.859 --> 35:19.033
Can you tell me your wife's name, Mr.
Solloway?

35:19.034 --> 35:21.572
Alison Bailey, but
she... we're not together.

35:21.573 --> 35:24.009
- Is she here?
- No.

35:24.010 --> 35:26.715
I believe she said a different name.

35:26.716 --> 35:28.251
- Helen.
- You're awake.

35:28.252 --> 35:29.955
- Told me you were sleeping.
- I just woke up.

35:29.956 --> 35:32.894
- You look okay. He looks okay.
- Feel like shit, actually.

35:32.895 --> 35:34.463
- Who told you I was here?
- Nina. I couldn't believe it.

35:34.464 --> 35:35.967
- I'm sorry.
- I almost thought that she

35:35.968 --> 35:37.604
- was joking.
- You said you were the wife?

35:37.605 --> 35:38.706
- She's my ex.
- Have the police arrived yet?

35:38.707 --> 35:39.908
- Police?
- They really

35:39.909 --> 35:41.410
- should have been here by now.
- Why?

35:41.411 --> 35:42.781
- Who did this to you?
- Who did what to me?

35:42.782 --> 35:45.085
Who stabbed you, Noah?

35:45.086 --> 35:46.755
What... what is she talking about?

35:46.756 --> 35:48.959
- Did I get stabbed?
- Why doesn't he know that?

35:48.960 --> 35:51.397
I'm-I'm very sorry, Mr. Solloway.

35:51.398 --> 35:54.671
You were attacked by
someone with a knife.

35:54.672 --> 35:56.274
You bled profusely.

35:56.275 --> 35:58.679
They took you to surgery where Dr.
Quittner

35:58.680 --> 36:00.115
closed the artery off.

36:00.116 --> 36:02.419
- Jesus.
- You were very lucky.

36:02.420 --> 36:04.691
The blade missed your airway,
and your jugular vein,

36:04.692 --> 36:06.294
and just nicked your artery.

36:06.295 --> 36:09.200
- Who did this to you?
- I don't know.

36:09.201 --> 36:10.870
I-I-I don't remember.

36:10.871 --> 36:12.874
- You can't remember anything?
- No.

36:12.875 --> 36:14.911
Well, why not? I mean
why can't he remember?

36:14.912 --> 36:16.782
I'm not sure, Mrs. Solloway.

36:16.783 --> 36:17.984
When is the surgeon coming back?

36:17.985 --> 36:19.554
'Cause I'd like to speak to him.

36:19.555 --> 36:21.457
They found you in some
student's apartment?

36:21.458 --> 36:22.994
I'm renting it.

36:22.995 --> 36:24.598
And you really don't remember anything?

36:24.599 --> 36:26.000
I remember washing
dishes late at night...

36:26.001 --> 36:27.236
Well, why were you
washing dishes so late?

36:27.237 --> 36:28.939
Could this have been an accident?

36:28.940 --> 36:31.177
- Maybe I f-fell or something.
- It was a knife, Noah.

36:31.178 --> 36:33.849
A fucking knife sliced into your throat.

36:35.186 --> 36:36.822
- Okay.
- Are you sure that

36:36.823 --> 36:39.260
he doesn't have any brain
damage or something?

36:39.261 --> 36:42.032
He had a CAT scan, and the
result came back normal.

36:42.033 --> 36:44.136
Somebody tried to kill you.
Do you understand?

36:44.137 --> 36:46.708
Can we come in now?

36:46.709 --> 36:49.280
Shit, Dad. Are you all right?

36:49.281 --> 36:53.555
Hey, kids. I've been better.
Everything's gonna be okay.

36:53.556 --> 36:55.526
Does this thing have a massage feature?

36:55.527 --> 36:57.462
Your dad's right. He's going to be fine.

36:57.463 --> 36:58.966
He should be home in a couple of days.

36:58.967 --> 37:01.003
He doesn't live with us.

37:01.004 --> 37:03.341
Um, Mr. Solloway,
I need to ask you

37:03.342 --> 37:04.911
a few more questions. I'm sorry.

37:04.912 --> 37:07.115
And then I'll let you rest.

37:07.116 --> 37:08.686
Can you tell me,

37:08.687 --> 37:10.856
do you have a history of
any previous surgeries?

37:10.857 --> 37:12.794
He had his appendix out ten years ago.

37:12.795 --> 37:14.496
That's it, unless you
count his wisdom teeth.

37:14.497 --> 37:16.033
- No.
- I think you were what,

37:16.034 --> 37:18.037
- 25 or 26?
- It's not relevant.

37:18.038 --> 37:19.975
- What about medications?
- No. He doesn't...

37:19.976 --> 37:21.645
- Are you currently taking any?
- He hates medication.

37:21.646 --> 37:22.880
He won't even take Tylenol
when he has a fever.

37:22.881 --> 37:25.318
- I'm on Vicodin.
- What?

37:25.319 --> 37:27.991
- Dosage?
- 7.5 milligrams.

37:27.992 --> 37:31.130
I had a shoulder injury.
I'm... the pain gets pretty bad.

37:31.131 --> 37:32.633
Is that getting worse?
Who's treating you?

37:32.634 --> 37:34.804
- I have a prescription, Helen.
- From who?

37:34.805 --> 37:36.641
That's all I need for now.

37:36.642 --> 37:38.812
Is there anything I can get for you, Mr.
Solloway?

37:38.813 --> 37:41.518
- No. Thank you very much.
- Can we go now?

37:41.519 --> 37:44.156
That's a good idea. Your
father could use some rest.

37:44.157 --> 37:45.993
Can you bring your
sister down to the cafeteria

37:45.994 --> 37:47.730
and get her something to eat and
I'll meet you guys there, okay?

37:47.731 --> 37:49.668
But I don't have any money.

37:52.340 --> 37:54.344
Nothing too sweet.

37:57.350 --> 37:58.418
Could you get a few more blankets?

37:58.419 --> 37:59.921
It's freezing in here.

37:59.922 --> 38:00.924
Sure.

38:08.205 --> 38:11.010
- What happened to you?
- Helen, I really need to sleep.

38:13.215 --> 38:16.855
You can stay, but just
please stop talking.

38:57.403 --> 38:59.807
<i>And I'll kill you! I'll show you!</i>

38:59.808 --> 39:02.312
<i>Hey, hey, hey! Break it up!
Break it up!</i>

39:06.221 --> 39:08.224
<i>Split it up, all right?</i>

39:08.225 --> 39:11.096
<i>You're both going to the hole next time!</i>

39:11.097 --> 39:12.465
<i>Relax!</i>

39:12.466 --> 39:15.371
- Hey, Solloway.
- Hey.

39:15.372 --> 39:18.378
Congratulations. Happy six months.

39:23.723 --> 39:25.426
Thanks.

39:27.496 --> 39:28.565
It's transparent.

39:28.566 --> 39:29.767
Right. Yeah.

39:29.768 --> 39:32.472
See if you got a shank, or contraband,

39:32.473 --> 39:33.775
or whatever, you know.

39:33.776 --> 39:35.746
It's good, right?

39:35.747 --> 39:37.182
- It's great.
- Yeah.

39:37.183 --> 39:38.852
Can you believe it?

39:38.853 --> 39:41.357
There's a place in Jersey
imports these things.

39:41.358 --> 39:43.528
Takes, like, months to get here.

39:43.529 --> 39:46.801
Prisoner got out last week
and just left it behind,

39:46.802 --> 39:50.677
so I thought that maybe,
you know, you could...

39:52.948 --> 39:54.449
I don't know how to thank you, man.

39:54.450 --> 39:56.353
Use it.

39:56.354 --> 39:57.657
- I will.
- All right.

39:57.658 --> 40:00.461
Yeah.

40:00.462 --> 40:04.136
Hey, I ordered your book.

40:04.137 --> 40:06.373
Am I gonna like it?

40:06.374 --> 40:07.878
Let me know.

40:09.414 --> 40:11.184
I will do.

40:21.404 --> 40:24.544
What, you thought I forgot you?

40:29.220 --> 40:31.090
Thank you.

40:31.091 --> 40:32.459
You're welcome.

40:54.237 --> 40:58.344
- Mr. Solloway.
- Yeah?

40:58.345 --> 41:00.849
- I'm Detective Stanton.
- Detective Romero.

41:00.850 --> 41:02.686
How you feeling? You all right?

41:02.687 --> 41:04.957
Not really. My head's pounding.

41:04.958 --> 41:06.293
Is that nurse anywhere?

41:06.294 --> 41:09.466
Um, she'll be back in a few minutes.

41:09.467 --> 41:12.807
Do you feel up to answering a
few questions in the meantime?

41:12.808 --> 41:15.077
Go ahead. Ask.

41:15.078 --> 41:16.280
Don't think I'll be
able to help you much.

41:16.281 --> 41:18.150
I don't remember a thing.

41:18.151 --> 41:21.457
Well, can you say what you do remember?

41:21.458 --> 41:23.929
I was at the sink washing dishes,

41:23.930 --> 41:27.903
and then I'm here being told
someone stabbed me in the neck.

41:27.904 --> 41:29.607
And you have no idea who
might have done that to you?

41:29.608 --> 41:31.477
- No.
- Look.

41:31.478 --> 41:32.746
We've been by the apartment,

41:32.747 --> 41:34.316
and we got our guys over there now.

41:34.317 --> 41:37.088
And so far we've seen no
signs of a forced entry,

41:37.089 --> 41:40.027
so would you happen to
recall whether or not

41:40.028 --> 41:41.129
you locked the door?

41:44.771 --> 41:46.808
I might have or not. I couldn't...

41:46.809 --> 41:48.712
why? Do you think this was a robbery?

41:48.713 --> 41:50.014
- Unlikely.
- Yeah.

41:50.015 --> 41:51.483
Not with the nature of the injury.

41:51.484 --> 41:53.120
The fact that he went
for the neck, I mean,

41:53.121 --> 41:55.124
that tells us that the assailant
meant to do real harm.

41:55.125 --> 41:57.997
- Yeah. Well, he succeeded.
- Mr. Solloway,

41:57.998 --> 42:00.670
we're treating this attack
as an attempted homicide.

42:02.172 --> 42:03.975
Jesus.

42:06.347 --> 42:07.416
What the fuck?

42:10.690 --> 42:12.793
What about the kid?

42:12.794 --> 42:15.632
- What kid?
- The frat guy.

42:15.633 --> 42:17.770
Regers or the guy I sublet...

42:17.771 --> 42:20.374
- Dan? Dan Regan?
- Right.

42:20.375 --> 42:22.145
Could they have been after him?

42:22.146 --> 42:24.382
Mr. Regan's at the station.
He's cooperating.

42:24.383 --> 42:26.521
Yeah, I mean, plus, you
know, like you say,

42:26.522 --> 42:28.959
he's a 20-year-old Delta Phi kid,

42:28.960 --> 42:30.996
and you just finished
three years at Fishkill.

42:30.997 --> 42:32.833
You're a public figure.

42:37.209 --> 42:40.214
So if either one of
you was gonna be targeted,

42:40.215 --> 42:41.350
we're gonna lean towards you.

42:41.351 --> 42:42.820
I mean, would you agree with that?

42:42.821 --> 42:44.724
- Fine.
- Try to think then.

42:44.725 --> 42:46.393
Is there anyone out there
that's got a gripe with you?

42:46.394 --> 42:48.565
Might want to harm you?

42:51.037 --> 42:55.746
What's your relationship like
with Cole Lockhart these days?

42:55.747 --> 42:58.585
- We don't have one.
- When's the last time

42:58.586 --> 43:00.221
you had any contact with Mr. Lockhart?

43:00.222 --> 43:03.293
I don't know. Years ago.

43:03.294 --> 43:04.964
The trial, I guess.

43:04.965 --> 43:06.901
- Brother's murder trial?
- Right.

43:06.902 --> 43:09.205
Yeah, well, between
what happened to his brother

43:09.206 --> 43:10.876
and the affair with his wife,

43:10.877 --> 43:14.049
Cole is definitely a person of interest.

43:14.050 --> 43:17.923
But, um, what about Alison Bailey?

43:20.697 --> 43:22.833
What about her?

43:22.834 --> 43:24.269
You're still married.

43:24.270 --> 43:27.442
- Yes.
- But estranged.

43:27.443 --> 43:30.247
Wow. You guys know everything
about me, don't you?

43:30.248 --> 43:33.053
Does she still have any
feelings left for you?

43:33.054 --> 43:35.291
How the fuck do I know?

43:35.292 --> 43:37.629
Well, what we're trying to figure out is

43:37.630 --> 43:40.869
if she'd have a problem with
you seeing other women.

43:40.870 --> 43:42.305
Lucky for her, I've been incarcerated

43:42.306 --> 43:44.109
the last three years,

43:44.110 --> 43:47.115
and since I got out I've
been a fucking monk, so...

43:47.116 --> 43:51.089
So, um, Ms., um, Le Gall?

43:52.259 --> 43:54.062
Ms. Le who?

43:54.063 --> 43:56.399
Yeah. Juliette Le Gall.

43:56.400 --> 43:58.571
The woman who found you
and brought you in.

44:02.146 --> 44:03.848
- Juliette found me?
- Yeah.

44:03.849 --> 44:08.257
Juliette found you at 1:38 a. m.

44:08.258 --> 44:11.531
What's your relationship with her?

44:11.532 --> 44:13.768
Well, we met yesterday.
I barely know her.

44:13.769 --> 44:15.872
And yet she was at your house at one...

44:15.873 --> 44:17.643
No, no, no. She wasn't at my house.

44:17.644 --> 44:20.549
I was at her house with several
other people, and then I left.

44:20.550 --> 44:21.818
Everything okay in here?

44:21.819 --> 44:23.120
Yeah, we're good.

44:23.121 --> 44:24.757
Yeah. We'll be done in just a minute.

44:24.758 --> 44:25.992
Look, Mr. Solloway, we're
all on the same side here.

44:25.993 --> 44:27.428
If you just relax...

44:27.429 --> 44:28.932
Relax? Someone tried to fucking kill me,

44:28.933 --> 44:30.735
and you got nothing.

44:30.736 --> 44:33.140
You have no fucking clue who
might actually have done this.

44:33.141 --> 44:35.277
- And when you say "actually"...
- Can you ask them to go?

44:35.278 --> 44:38.016
Just go and do their jobs?

44:38.017 --> 44:39.620
Will you do that for me, please?

44:39.621 --> 44:42.291
I... maybe you
can come back later?

44:42.292 --> 44:43.595
- Okay.
- Yeah, yeah.

44:43.596 --> 44:45.599
Get some rest, Mr. Solloway.

44:50.610 --> 44:52.679
Buzz me when it's filled up.

45:00.195 --> 45:01.899
Thanks a lot.

45:06.842 --> 45:08.477
You're coming home with me.

45:08.478 --> 45:11.349
- Nina, no.
- And why not?

45:11.350 --> 45:12.686
'Cause for all I know
your husband's the one

45:12.687 --> 45:14.422
- who tried to kill me.
- Please.

45:14.423 --> 45:17.129
JP's not smart enough to
get away with murder.

45:29.721 --> 45:32.458
Who the hell lives here?

45:32.459 --> 45:35.632
A friend.

45:35.633 --> 45:38.003
Really? You just got stabbed.

45:38.004 --> 45:39.807
Now you want to go get a booty call?

45:39.808 --> 45:44.817
Apparently she... apparently
she saved my life.

45:44.818 --> 45:47.421
What was she doing at your
apartment at midnight?

45:47.422 --> 45:49.159
I don't know.

45:52.934 --> 45:55.437
I'll wait. I'll take you home after.

45:55.438 --> 45:58.878
No, no, I'm gonna be okay.
You just go home.

45:58.879 --> 46:00.850
I'll... I'll call you tomorrow.

46:04.624 --> 46:08.865
Nina, what are you doing?

46:08.866 --> 46:12.672
I'm crying, you asshole.

46:12.673 --> 46:15.846
Come on. You don't cry. You're
the tough one, remember?

46:21.691 --> 46:22.826
Fucking take them, Noah.

46:24.163 --> 46:26.266
Take them. He left the house to you.

46:26.267 --> 46:28.103
- I don't want it.
- I don't either.

46:28.104 --> 46:30.274
- Well, then fucking sell it.
- I can't.

46:30.275 --> 46:33.346
- Why not?
- You know why.

46:33.347 --> 46:36.453
Nina, I am 50 years old.

46:36.454 --> 46:39.893
You can stop apologizing to me now.

46:39.894 --> 46:43.433
Right. Well, that's...
that's your psychosis.

46:43.434 --> 46:46.106
I'm fine.

46:46.107 --> 46:48.443
- Really?
- It was 30 years ago.

46:48.444 --> 46:50.214
Let's move on.

46:50.215 --> 46:53.221
Well, you're certainly really
good at that, aren't you?

47:39.479 --> 47:42.351
I thought you were the
detectives with more questions.

47:42.352 --> 47:46.760
- They've already been here?
- Just like a TV show.

47:46.761 --> 47:51.102
The younger one even carried
a cup of takeout coffee.

47:51.103 --> 47:53.641
That must have been exciting, right?

47:53.642 --> 47:55.945
Didn't you say you were bored?

47:55.946 --> 47:58.784
Ha.

47:58.785 --> 48:01.658
This is okay?

48:13.281 --> 48:16.019
You must have been frightened.

48:16.020 --> 48:20.995
I actually don't remember it happening.

48:20.996 --> 48:23.000
Strange.

48:27.275 --> 48:29.813
I'm afraid I've also forgotten...

48:29.814 --> 48:33.153
why you were there.

48:33.154 --> 48:36.160
You didn't forget. You
weren't expecting me.

48:48.417 --> 48:50.889
I'm sorry to have scared you.

48:53.494 --> 48:57.434
Honestly, I wasn't scared.

48:57.435 --> 49:00.207
I was angry.

49:00.208 --> 49:03.079
- Why?
- I don't know.

49:03.080 --> 49:07.522
I guess I was hoping that you...

49:07.523 --> 49:11.497
that this wouldn't be so complicated.

49:27.095 --> 49:29.098
Are you all right?

49:29.099 --> 49:30.836
<i>Oui.</i>

49:33.174 --> 49:35.178
<i>Bonne nuit.</i>

49:56.721 --> 50:01.329
I imagine the doctors told
you not to strain yourself.

50:01.330 --> 50:03.767
They say that to everybody.

50:07.141 --> 50:09.245
I make it a rule never
to sleep with a man

50:09.246 --> 50:13.521
after being interrogated
for his attempted murder.

50:13.522 --> 50:16.492
